# MISSION: Senior News Intelligence Architect (Gatopardo Aesthetic)

## 1. UI/UX: "THE DARK EDITORIAL"
- **Theme:** Use deep Onyx (#050505) with 12px Glassmorphism overlays.
- **Typography:** Headlines must be Serif (Playfair Display). Body must be clean Sans-Serif (Inter).
- **Layout:** Implement "The Prestige Grid"—one massive 3D-tilting hero card followed by an asymmetrical bento grid.
- **Components:** Add a "Summarize" button on every card that triggers a streaming AI overlay.

## 2. THE ENGINE: FEEDBACK LOOP & SPEED
- **Scraping:** Use Firecrawl or Playwright. Every fetch must use a `try-catch` feedback loop.
- **Feedback Loop:** If a scrape fails, log the error to `logs/crawler_errors.json`. On the next run, the agent must read this file and attempt a different scraping strategy (e.g., swapping headers or using a proxy).
- **Parallelism:** Use `Promise.all` for simultaneous multi-source scanning.

## 3. INTELLIGENCE & SUMMARIZATION
- **Logic:** Summaries must use the "3-3-1 Protocol": 3 hard facts, 3 key entities (people/orgs), and 1 "Why this matters" impact statement.
- **Direct Linking:** Every summary must contain a primary action button linking to the `original_source_url`.

## 4. TECH STACK & @DOCS
- Reference Tailwind CSS v4, Framer Motion (for transitions), Vercel AI SDK, Firecrawl, and Lucide.
- **Cursor indexed docs (Settings → Features → Docs → + Add New Doc):** paste each URL once so @Docs can retrieve them:
  - Vercel AI SDK: https://sdk.vercel.ai/docs/llms-full.txt
  - Tailwind CSS v4: https://tailwindcss.com/docs
  - Firecrawl: https://docs.firecrawl.dev
  - Framer Motion: https://www.framer.com/motion/
  - Lucide Icons: https://lucide.dev/guide
